(36, 3, 'Thomas W.', 'tomwarf@gmail.fr', '', '95.208.61.225', '2009-05-12 21:59:33', '2009-05-12 18:59:33', 'I automated file uploads with the iMacros addon (FF and IE!): http://www.iopus.com/imacros/firefox/\r\nSome of my tests use Selenium, others run in iMacros...', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.9.0.5) Gecko/2008120122 Firefox/3.0.5 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0),
(35, 11, 'vic', 'pikyyrx@yahoo.com', '', '202.159.18.10', '2009-05-11 05:49:41', '2009-05-11 02:49:41', 'its. work!! thx very much', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042316 Firefox/3.0.10', '', 0, 0),
(5, 18, 'Christian', 'christian.helmbold@yahoo.de', '', '212.80.224.243', '2009-05-05 07:33:26', '2009-05-05 04:33:26', 'Take a look at Apache Wicket! Wicket uses clean and pure Java code and pure HTML. Programming with Wicket feels very natural with wicket. Creating new components is so easy that sometimes you don''t realize that you have just creaated a new one.\r\n\r\nI''ve tested several web frameworks, but none of them was so consistent, easy to use and to debug. You feel the weaknesses of most frameworks when you create your own components, use AJAX or debug your application. All this is really comfortable with Wicket. You can simply read pure Java code an understand you application.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (X11; U; Linux i686; de; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042523 Ubuntu/8.10 (intrepid) Firefox/3.0.10', '', 0, 0),
(6, 18, 'Kenneth', 'kennethmark8888@yahoo.com', '', '202.175.77.106', '2009-05-05 07:37:22', '2009-05-05 04:37:22', 'I''ve got same experience by using Seam and reach a point that I''ve to leave it. As the application grows those downside effects really hurt us a lot.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.9) Gecko/2009040821 Firefox/3.0.9 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0),
(63, 16, 'Red Five', 'red_five@charter.net', '', '24.151.231.199', '2009-06-18 21:58:22', '2009-06-18 18:58:22', 'There''s a simpler way: simply make your stamp_updated column first, and set its "on update" attribute to current_timestamp, with no default value. Then follow with your stamp_created column, and set nothing for default value or "on update". Timestamp values default to the current timestamp, according to http://www.haidongji.com/2009/01/04/interesting-things-about-timestamp-data-type-in-mysql/.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (X11; U; Linux x86_64; en-US; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042523 Ubuntu/9.04 (jaunty) Firefox/3.0.10', '', 0, 0),
(64, 16, 'Red Five', 'red_five@charter.net', '', '24.151.231.199', '2009-06-18 22:01:58', '2009-06-18 19:01:58', 'Oops, misread the default value thing. I just tried it, and by default it''ll insert a timestamp value of ''0000-00-00 00:00:00''.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (X11; U; Linux x86_64; en-US; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042523 Ubuntu/9.04 (jaunty) Firefox/3.0.10', '', 0, 0),
(14, 18, 'Pete Muir', 'pete.muir@jboss.org', 'http://in.relation.to/Bloggers/Pete', '82.41.244.26', '2009-05-05 19:03:31', '2009-05-05 16:03:31', 'Good feedback:\r\n\r\n* Utility methods - you can still write your utility methods as plain Java methods, and wire them in yourself - use as little or as much DI as you like\r\n* IDE / EL usage - we totally agree, hence why we have worked hard on JSR-299 which is typesafe, and so supported natively by an IDE (you can just use the standard "find implementations" feature to navigate, extensions can help with binding annotations)\r\n* JSF debugging - we''ve tried to take our experience with this to JSF2 - so please try out JSF2 and see what you think - of course, this is a first iteration of the new support, so we need feedback on that\r\n* Exception handling - we definitely realise this is a weak point (mainly due to having to bolt this onto JSF), but JSF2 now has native exception handling so hopefully this will address your concerns.\r\n\r\nPete (Seam project lead)', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-GB; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042315 Firefox/3.0.10', '', 0, 0),
(15, 18, 'Bogdan', 'agresso@gmail.com', 'http://gusiev.com', '92.49.198.230', '2009-05-05 19:28:01', '2009-05-05 16:28:01', 'I can not do utility method call from JSF template. That is why I have to use Seam Application context for utility class. That is a problem because I can not find all usages of the utility method call.\r\n\r\nThanks for your info - it was really helpful. I will look through JSF2 of course.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; ru; rv:1.9.0.6) Gecko/2009011913 Firefox/3.0.6 WebMoney Advisor', '', 0, 1),
(16, 18, 'Pete Muir', 'pete.muir@jboss.org', 'http://in.relation.to/Bloggers/Pete', '82.41.244.26', '2009-05-05 19:41:05', '2009-05-05 16:41:05', 'Aha - I see what you mean - in general, I would advise calling only business methods from JSF, and using these to call utility methods.\r\n\r\nA good tooling solution (like JBoss Tools) will alieveate this tottally, as it extends the IDE searches to include EL.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-GB; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042315 Firefox/3.0.10', '', 0, 0),
(17, 18, 'Max', 'max.andersen@redhat.com', 'http://jboss.org/tools', '83.79.93.1', '2009-05-05 19:41:41', '2009-05-05 16:41:41', 'Bogdan, JBoss Tools 3 have "Find references" that also reports usage of EL in xhtml, pages.xml etc.\r\n\r\nLet us know if there is something we don''t find ;)', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 6.1; Trident/4.0; SLCC2; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30729; Media Center PC 6.0)', '', 0, 0),
(18, 18, 'Max', 'max.andersen@redhat.com', 'http://jboss.org/tools', '83.79.93.1', '2009-05-05 19:42:12', '2009-05-05 16:42:12', 'Whoops forgot to say I''m JBoss Tools lead', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 6.1; Trident/4.0; SLCC2; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30729; Media Center PC 6.0)', '', 0, 0),
(19, 18, 'Bogdan', 'agresso@gmail.com', 'http://gusiev.com', '92.49.198.230', '2009-05-05 19:50:29', '2009-05-05 16:50:29', 'Max,\r\nCan I integrate these tools to IDE? \r\nI prefer IntelliJ Idea.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; ru; rv:1.9.0.6) Gecko/2009011913 Firefox/3.0.6 WebMoney Advisor', '', 0, 2),
(20, 18, 'Bogdan', 'agresso@gmail.com', 'http://gusiev.com', '92.49.198.230', '2009-05-05 19:59:51', '2009-05-05 16:59:51', 'Pete,\r\n`Permission` methods alway get me stuck. \r\nCurrently I am doing the call like this for them:\r\n<% if (object.isUserAllowedEdit(getCurrentUserId()) {%>\r\n....\r\n<% } %> \r\nI know that it is bad idea even if don''t use Seam.\r\nWhat do you recommend in this case?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; ru; rv:1.9.0.6) Gecko/2009011913 Firefox/3.0.6 WebMoney Advisor', '', 0, 2),
