(118, 29, 'Sean Crotty', 'scrotty@gmail.com', '', '76.120.40.213', '2009-12-01 03:30:52', '2009-12-01 00:30:52', 'You should try the IDE Vim plugins - it''s the best of both worlds.\r\n\r\nIntelliJ has IdeaVim (http://ideavim.sourceforge.net/)\r\nEclipse has viplugin (http://www.viplugin.com/viplugin/)\r\n\r\n\r\nThey are both very good and allow you to do the "basic things" in a VIM-way, while still allowing you to do things like "Go to Definition" too.\r\n\r\nEven better, they allow you to map things like "Go to Definition" to VIM-like keystrokes. For example, I use gd for "Go to Definition" of the method that the caret is currently in.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.5) Gecko/20091102 Firefox/3.5.5 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0),
