(808, 23, 'backlinks', 'Blowe@yahoo.com', 'http://backlinkcenter.nl', '76.73.56.217', '2011-05-16 13:35:22', '2011-05-16 10:35:22', 'There are some fascinating deadlines on this article however I don’t know if I see all of them middle to heart. There is some validity however I''ll take hold opinion till I look into it further. Good article , thanks and we wish extra! Added to FeedBurner as nicely', 0, 'spam', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 6.1; Trident/4.0)', '', 0, 0),
(443, 40, 'antono', 'antono.vasiljev@gmail.com', 'http://antono.info/', '93.84.220.59', '2010-08-27 02:46:25', '2010-08-26 23:46:25', 'BTW now i think that factories is a good idea for db population :)', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (X11; U; Linux i686; en-US) AppleWebKit/534.6 (KHTML, like Gecko) Ubuntu/10.04 Chromium/7.0.505.0 Chrome/7.0.505.0 Safari/534.6', '', 0, 0),
(463, 33, 'szeryf', 'szeryf74@gmail.com', 'http://szeryf.wordpress.com/', '192.138.116.231', '2010-08-31 11:22:55', '2010-08-31 08:22:55', 'The `private'' implementation makes sense when you take into account that in Ruby you don''t "call methods", you "send messages" to other objects. That''s why it doesn''t matter if the other object has the same type as the one that sends the message (technically, it may not even be true, if the other objects has undergone some monkey patching). Although I consider the fact that you can''t send private messages to self to be a bug -- Ruby should "know" that self is self :)', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; pl; rv:1.9.2.8) Gecko/20100722 Firefox/3.6.8 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0),
(543, 11, 'Gigi', 'djdablitz@yahoo.com', 'http://none', '81.196.74.79', '2010-09-15 23:18:07', '2010-09-15 20:18:07', 'hi,\r\n\r\ni want NOT to clear the input file field when i press "submit". how can i do this?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.9) Gecko/20100824 Firefox/3.6.9', '', 0, 0),
