(89, 0, 'rss_867bd5c64f85878d03a060509cd2f92c', 'O:9:"magpierss":18:{s:6:"parser";i:0;s:12:"current_item";a:0:{}s:5:"items";a:50:{i:0;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:36:"WPCandy: The making of an Obox Theme";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=16844";s:4:"link";s:81:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/dE3pahDwE3Y/the-making-of-an-obox-theme";s:11:"description";s:671:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/watches/the-making-of-an-obox-theme"><em>Click here to view the embedded video.</em></a></p><p>Josh Hemsley was asked if he could give a behind-the-scenes look when designing an upcoming theme for Obox Design, which they have named <em>WrdPrss</em>. In the words of David Perel, <q>take a look at the video and look forward to the awesome coming your way soon!</q></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16844">The making of an Obox Theme</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 11 Apr 2011 18:56:17 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:15:"Mark McWilliams";}s:7:"summary";s:671:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/watches/the-making-of-an-obox-theme"><em>Click here to view the embedded video.</em></a></p><p>Josh Hemsley was asked if he could give a behind-the-scenes look when designing an upcoming theme for Obox Design, which they have named <em>WrdPrss</em>. In the words of David Perel, <q>take a look at the video and look forward to the awesome coming your way soon!</q></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16844">The making of an Obox Theme</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";}i:1;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:28:"Matt: Bloomberg TV Interview";s:4:"guid";s:21:"http://ma.tt/?p=37956";s:4:"link";s:44:"http://ma.tt/2011/04/bloomberg-tv-interview/";s:11:"description";s:246:"<p>At SxSW last month I was interviewed by <a href="https://twitter.com/crisvalerio">Cris Valerio</a> from <a href="http://www.bloomberg.com/video/68075030/">Bloomberg TV</a>. The interview aired recently and you check it out below:</p>\n<p></p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 11 Apr 2011 17:22:28 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:4:"Matt";}s:7:"summary";s:246:"<p>At SxSW last month I was interviewed by <a href="https://twitter.com/crisvalerio">Cris Valerio</a> from <a href="http://www.bloomberg.com/video/68075030/">Bloomberg TV</a>. The interview aired recently and you check it out below:</p>\n<p></p>";}i:2;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:58:"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Theme Releases for 4/11";s:4:"guid";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=9873";s:4:"link";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/H1OLVz-8RMI/";s:11:"description";s:913:"<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-9874" title="ribbons" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/ribbons.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="113" /></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.wpexplorer.com/ribbons-wordpress-theme.html"><strong>Ribbons</strong></a> is a very clean and modern free WordPress theme that comes with a ribbon focused design that gives it a cool &#8220;3d&#8221; effect and it includes a built-in jQuery Cycle slider.</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-9875" title="springfloral" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/springfloral.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="113" /></p>\n<p><a href="http://emptynestthemes.emptynestheritage.com/?p=746"><strong>Spring Floral</strong></a> is a green-based theme with a left sidebar.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/H1OLVz-8RMI" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 11 Apr 2011 13:00:48 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:10:"James Huff";}s:7:"summary";s:913:"<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-9874" title="ribbons" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/ribbons.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="113" /></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.wpexplorer.com/ribbons-wordpress-theme.html"><strong>Ribbons</strong></a> is a very clean and modern free WordPress theme that comes with a ribbon focused design that gives it a cool &#8220;3d&#8221; effect and it includes a built-in jQuery Cycle slider.</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-9875" title="springfloral" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/springfloral.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="113" /></p>\n<p><a href="http://emptynestthemes.emptynestheritage.com/?p=746"><strong>Spring Floral</strong></a> is a green-based theme with a left sidebar.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/H1OLVz-8RMI" height="1" width="1" />";}i:3;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:62:"WPCandy: Best of the Rest: WordPress News for April 11th, 2011";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=16825";s:4:"link";s:80:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/dgfeJZrkbJE/2011-4-11-best-of-the-rest";s:11:"description";s:4772:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16825"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16826" title="Best of the Rest, chocolate box (teaser)" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/bestoftherest-teaser.png" alt="" width="600" height="240" /></a></p><p>Believe it or not, the WordPress community is a pretty big one. While we try our best to cover all of the <a title="WordPress News" href="http://wpcandy.com/reports">WordPress news</a> we can—and I would argue we do a pretty good job—we can&#8217;t always cover everything that happens each week. We&#8217;re only human, of course.</p><p>To remedy the news we miss, I&#8217;m happy to introduce a new recurring post on WPCandy called &#8220;Best of the Rest&#8221;. In these posts we&#8217;ll run through the news we couldn&#8217;t quite get to the week before.</p><p><span id="more-16825"></span></p><h3>Jason Schuller launches Customyze.me for theme customizations</h3><p><a href="http://www.customyze.me/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16830" title="Customyze.me logo" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/Screen-shot-2011-04-11-at-6.05.06-AM.png" alt="" width="371" height="85" /></a></p><p>Jason Schuller, of Press75 and Theme Garden fame, launched <a title="Customyze.me" href="http://www.customyze.me/">Customyze.me</a> using his latest theme launch. Anyone can use this new site to request theme customizations.</p><h3>Achievements for BuddyPress 2.0.7 is now available</h3><p>Paul Gibbs has released the latest version of his BuddyPress Achievements plugin. You can read the release notes <a title="Achievements for BuddyPress update notes" href="http://achievementsapp.com/2011/04/03/achievements-for-buddypress-2-0-7-available/">on his blog</a>.</p><h3>New PollDaddy personalized URLs</h3><p><a href="http://blog.polldaddy.com/2011/03/25/new-feature-personalized-survey-permalinks/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-5812" title="Polldaddy" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2010/10/polldaddy-logo.png" alt="" width="600" height="100" /></a></p><p>In addition to the PollDaddy domain mapping, they&#8217;ve introduced a method for c<a title="Custom PollDaddy urls" href="http://blog.polldaddy.com/2011/03/25/new-feature-personalized-survey-permalinks/">ustomizing the standard PollDaddy poll URLs</a>.</p><h3>Free Headway Leafs are now available in the Plugin Directory</h3><p><a href="http://headwaythemes.com/news/free-leafs-in-plugin-directory/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16831" title="Free Headway Leafs in the Plugin Directory" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/headwayleaf-teaser.png" alt="" width="600" height="104" /></a></p><p>The folks at Headway Themes have <a title="Headway Themes free Leafs added to the Plugin Directory" href="http://headwaythemes.com/news/free-leafs-in-plugin-directory/">added all of their free Leafs</a> to the WordPress Plugin Directory.</p><h3>New Social Karma plugin adds icons as links next to your links</h3><p>Mark Bloomfeld has released a <a title="Social Karma WordPress plugin" href="http://mark.bloomfield.co.za/?p=364  ">new WordPress plugin</a> that, using shortcodes, adds social links next to whatever you&#8217;re linking up in your content.</p><h3>New Roots theme framework brings all the wonderful buzzwords</h3><p><a href="http://www.rootstheme.com/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16833" title="Roots theme buzzword glory" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/Screen-shot-2011-04-11-at-6.35.04-AM.png" alt="" width="486" height="109" /></a></p><p>Ben Word&#8217;s new <a title="Roost WordPress theme framework" href="http://www.rootstheme.com/">Roots theme framework</a> incorporates HTML5 Boilerplate, Starkers, and Boilerplate CSS. It&#8217;s free, and development is being managed on Github.</p><h3>New Atlas theme framework looking for beta testers</h3><p><a href="http://cranesandskyhooks.com/articles/become-an-atlas-beta-tester/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16834" title="Atlas theme framework" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/Screen-shot-2011-04-11-at-6.39.45-AM.png" alt="" width="542" height="81" /></a></p><p>Donal MacArthur&#8217;s development business Cranes &amp; Skyhooks has been working on a new theme framework called Atlas. He is looking for beta testers to test it out, so if you&#8217;re interested you should <a title="Beta testing Atlas WordPress theme" href="http://cranesandskyhooks.com/articles/become-an-atlas-beta-tester/">get in touch</a> with him.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16825">Best of the Rest: WordPress News for April 11th, 2011</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 11 Apr 2011 10:46:30 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"Ryan Imel";}s:7:"summary";s:4772:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16825"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16826" title="Best of the Rest, chocolate box (teaser)" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/bestoftherest-teaser.png" alt="" width="600" height="240" /></a></p><p>Believe it or not, the WordPress community is a pretty big one. While we try our best to cover all of the <a title="WordPress News" href="http://wpcandy.com/reports">WordPress news</a> we can—and I would argue we do a pretty good job—we can&#8217;t always cover everything that happens each week. We&#8217;re only human, of course.</p><p>To remedy the news we miss, I&#8217;m happy to introduce a new recurring post on WPCandy called &#8220;Best of the Rest&#8221;. In these posts we&#8217;ll run through the news we couldn&#8217;t quite get to the week before.</p><p><span id="more-16825"></span></p><h3>Jason Schuller launches Customyze.me for theme customizations</h3><p><a href="http://www.customyze.me/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16830" title="Customyze.me logo" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/Screen-shot-2011-04-11-at-6.05.06-AM.png" alt="" width="371" height="85" /></a></p><p>Jason Schuller, of Press75 and Theme Garden fame, launched <a title="Customyze.me" href="http://www.customyze.me/">Customyze.me</a> using his latest theme launch. Anyone can use this new site to request theme customizations.</p><h3>Achievements for BuddyPress 2.0.7 is now available</h3><p>Paul Gibbs has released the latest version of his BuddyPress Achievements plugin. You can read the release notes <a title="Achievements for BuddyPress update notes" href="http://achievementsapp.com/2011/04/03/achievements-for-buddypress-2-0-7-available/">on his blog</a>.</p><h3>New PollDaddy personalized URLs</h3><p><a href="http://blog.polldaddy.com/2011/03/25/new-feature-personalized-survey-permalinks/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-5812" title="Polldaddy" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2010/10/polldaddy-logo.png" alt="" width="600" height="100" /></a></p><p>In addition to the PollDaddy domain mapping, they&#8217;ve introduced a method for c<a title="Custom PollDaddy urls" href="http://blog.polldaddy.com/2011/03/25/new-feature-personalized-survey-permalinks/">ustomizing the standard PollDaddy poll URLs</a>.</p><h3>Free Headway Leafs are now available in the Plugin Directory</h3><p><a href="http://headwaythemes.com/news/free-leafs-in-plugin-directory/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16831" title="Free Headway Leafs in the Plugin Directory" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/headwayleaf-teaser.png" alt="" width="600" height="104" /></a></p><p>The folks at Headway Themes have <a title="Headway Themes free Leafs added to the Plugin Directory" href="http://headwaythemes.com/news/free-leafs-in-plugin-directory/">added all of their free Leafs</a> to the WordPress Plugin Directory.</p><h3>New Social Karma plugin adds icons as links next to your links</h3><p>Mark Bloomfeld has released a <a title="Social Karma WordPress plugin" href="http://mark.bloomfield.co.za/?p=364  ">new WordPress plugin</a> that, using shortcodes, adds social links next to whatever you&#8217;re linking up in your content.</p><h3>New Roots theme framework brings all the wonderful buzzwords</h3><p><a href="http://www.rootstheme.com/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16833" title="Roots theme buzzword glory" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/Screen-shot-2011-04-11-at-6.35.04-AM.png" alt="" width="486" height="109" /></a></p><p>Ben Word&#8217;s new <a title="Roost WordPress theme framework" href="http://www.rootstheme.com/">Roots theme framework</a> incorporates HTML5 Boilerplate, Starkers, and Boilerplate CSS. It&#8217;s free, and development is being managed on Github.</p><h3>New Atlas theme framework looking for beta testers</h3><p><a href="http://cranesandskyhooks.com/articles/become-an-atlas-beta-tester/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16834" title="Atlas theme framework" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/Screen-shot-2011-04-11-at-6.39.45-AM.png" alt="" width="542" height="81" /></a></p><p>Donal MacArthur&#8217;s development business Cranes &amp; Skyhooks has been working on a new theme framework called Atlas. He is looking for beta testers to test it out, so if you&#8217;re interested you should <a title="Beta testing Atlas WordPress theme" href="http://cranesandskyhooks.com/articles/become-an-atlas-beta-tester/">get in touch</a> with him.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16825">Best of the Rest: WordPress News for April 11th, 2011</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";}i:4;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:87:"WPCandy: Jason Schuller interviewed about web design on the Freelance Jam video podcast";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=16816";s:4:"link";s:97:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/ICcY4uzi4No/jason-schuller-interviewed-about-web-design";s:11:"description";s:846:"<p></p><p>Jason Schuller, of <a href="http://press75.com/">Press75</a> and <a href="http://www.themegarden.com/">Theme Garden</a>, was <a href="http://freelancejam.com/3-web-design-process-with-jason-schuller/">interviewed</a> on the <a href="http://wpcandy.com/reports/the-freelancejam-podcast" title="Recently launched Freelance Jam">recently launched Freelance Jam</a> video podcast. They discussed the design process behind Schuller&#8217;s themes, where he gets his ideas, and how he translates them to the screen.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16816">Jason Schuller interviewed about web design on the Freelance Jam video podcast</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 11 Apr 2011 07:05:35 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"Ryan Imel";}s:7:"summary";s:846:"<p></p><p>Jason Schuller, of <a href="http://press75.com/">Press75</a> and <a href="http://www.themegarden.com/">Theme Garden</a>, was <a href="http://freelancejam.com/3-web-design-process-with-jason-schuller/">interviewed</a> on the <a href="http://wpcandy.com/reports/the-freelancejam-podcast" title="Recently launched Freelance Jam">recently launched Freelance Jam</a> video podcast. They discussed the design process behind Schuller&#8217;s themes, where he gets his ideas, and how he translates them to the screen.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16816">Jason Schuller interviewed about web design on the Freelance Jam video podcast</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";}i:5;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:53:"WPCandy: Vote here: Theme Madness 2011, Round 1 Day 1";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=16735";s:4:"link";s:93:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/V7JrV2Rsp7E/theme-madness-2011-round-1-day-1-voting";s:11:"description";s:14295:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16735"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16786" title="WPCandy Theme Madness voting, round 1 day 1" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/thememadnessround1day1-teaser.png" alt="" width="600" height="240" /></a></p><p>This week we will be running through Round 1 of Theme Madness, with eight games happening each day. Today&#8217;s games will be:</p><ul><li><span><a title="WooThemes" href="http://www.woothemes.com/">WooThemes</a> vs. <a title="Themeopoly" href="http://themeopoly.com/">Themeopoly</a></span></li><li><span><a title="Theme Team" href="http://gothemeteam.com/">Theme Team</a> vs. <a title="AppThemes" href="http://www.appthemes.com/">AppThemes</a></span></li><li><span><a title="ThemeForest" href="http://themeforest.net/">ThemeForest</a> vs. <a title="BioThemes" href="http://biothemes.com/">BioThemes</a></span></li><li><span><a title="Gabfire Themes" href="http://www.gabfire.com/">Gabfire Themes</a> vs. <a title="RichWP" href="http://richwp.com/">RichWP</a></span></li><li><span><a title="StudioPress" href="http://studiopress.com">StudioPress</a> vs. <a title="Themebaker" href="http://www.themebaker.com/">Themebaker</a></span></li><li><span><a title="FlexiThemes" href="http://flexithemes.com/">FlexiThemes</a> vs. <a title="PremiumPress" href="http://premiumpress.com/">PremiumPress</a></span></li><li><span><a title="Obox Themes" href="http://oboxthemes.com/">Obox Themes</a> vs. <a title="Signature Theme" href="http://signaturetheme.com/">Signature Theme</a></span></li><li><span><a title="BandThemer" href="http://bandthemer.com/">BandThemer</a> vs. <a title="UpThemes" href="http://upthemes.com/">UpThemes</a></span></li></ul><p>All of the polls and instructions can be found just after the jump, so be sure to click through to have your voice heard. Voting will take place for the next 48 hours, and close at midnight on the 12th (Eastern Standard Time).</p><p>If you need a reminder, the rules can be found <a title="How to win your Theme Madness 2011 Trophy" href="http://wpcandy.com/announces/theme-madness-2011-rules">here</a>. Good luck to everyone playing!</p><p><span id="more-16735"></span></p><h3>WooThemes vs. Themeopoly</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4872663"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4872663"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4872663/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">survey software</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><span><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="WooThemes on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/woothemes">@WooThemes</a> or <a title="Themeopoly" href="http://twitter.com/themeopoly">@Themeopoly</a>.</span></li><li><span><strong>The home game:</strong> If either WooThemes or Themeopoly start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</span></li></ul><h3>Theme Team vs. AppThemes</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4872713"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4872713"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4872713/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">survey software</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="Theme Team on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/themeteam">@ThemeTeam</a> or <a title="AppThemes" href="http://twitter.com/appthemes">@AppThemes</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either Theme Team or AppThemes start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>ThemeForest vs. BioThemes</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4872718"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4872718"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4872718/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">survey software</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="ThemeForest and Envato Web Design on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/envatowebdesign">@envatowebdesign</a> or <a title="BioThemes" href="http://twitter.com/biothemes">@BioThemes</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either ThemeForest or BioThemes start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>Gabfire Themes vs. RichWP</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4884211"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4884211"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4884211/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">online surveys</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="Gabfire Themes on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/gabfirethemes">@GabfireThemes</a> or <a title="RichWP on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/richwp">@RichWP</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either Gabfire Themes or RichWP start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>StudioPress vs. Themebaker</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4884218"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4884218"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4884218/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">survey software</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="StudioPress on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/studiopress">@StudioPress</a> or <a title="Themebaker on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/themebaker">@Themebaker</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either StudioPress or Themebaker start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>FlexiThemes vs. PremiumPress</h3><p><a name="pd_a_488